metadata.indicator_name: Rate of growth of Total Annual Gross Domestic Product (GDP) at constant prices
metadata.definition:
The percentage change of the Gross Domestic Product at 2018 constant prices, between two consecutive years.
Regional and subregional totals based on available data for the countries of the region.
metadata.calculation_methodology:
The methodology adopted for preparing the region's national accounts at constant 2018 prices consists of backcasting and extrapolating 2018 values at current prices with the respective volume indices by GDP  obtained from the official series. This produces a discrepancy which is explicitly included in the corresponding table.

The growth rate for the year t is calculated by obtaining the ratio between the aggregate's values in t and (t-1), subtracting one from that value, and finally multiplying by 100.
